You know what I hate?

00:00:01.080 --> 00:00:02.520
Everything.

00:00:05.340 --> 00:00:07.440
Wow, ok. Someone's in a dark place.

00:00:08.020 --> 00:00:11.480
Uh, sure. What I was gonna say is overthinking.

00:00:11.700 --> 00:00:13.880
It probably comes as no surprise to anyone who knows me,

00:00:13.880 --> 00:00:15.300
but I overthink everything.

00:00:15.960 --> 00:00:19.020
Anything, really, and sometimes I can't help it

00:00:19.020 --> 00:00:25.000
because engaging in self-reflection and expressing my findings is kind of what I do for a living. I mean it's what I'm doing right now.

00:00:25.320 --> 00:00:28.760
But I do know that there is a very very healthy line between

00:00:28.820 --> 00:00:35.480
insightful introspection and just overthinking like hell, and the negative effects are really bad

00:00:35.480 --> 00:00:39.960
I mean seriously, studies have shown that rumination leads to depression, anxiety,

00:00:40.020 --> 00:00:44.060
binge drinking, binge eating, inability to sleep and self-harm.

00:00:44.070 --> 00:00:50.399
I have had every single symptom of the danger of dwelling and yet I can't quite kick the habit of it.

00:00:50.500 --> 00:00:55.860
Especially when it's silly, even when it's silly like analyzing the punctuation of a text message.

00:00:55.860 --> 00:00:57.500
*Classical music*

00:00:57.500 --> 00:00:59.340
*phone beeps*
*classical music continues*

00:00:59.340 --> 00:01:06.060
*classical music continues*

